org.apache.spark.sql.api.java

Class ArrayType

  • Object
    • org.apache.spark.sql.api.java.DataType
      • org.apache.spark.sql.api.java.ArrayType

  • public class ArrayType
extends DataType
    The data type representing Lists. An ArrayType object comprises two fields, DataType elementType and boolean containsNull. The field of elementType is used to specify the type of array elements. The field of containsNull is used to specify if the array has null values. To create an ArrayType, DataType.createArrayType(DataType) or DataType.createArrayType(DataType, boolean) should be used.
